# Git diff enhancements.
#
# Route binary-image diffs through a text-preview driver so `git diff`,
# `git log -p`, and IDE diff views (VS Code's built-in diff, PR review
# surfaces, etc.) show *something* useful instead of "Binary file not
# shown". The actual preview command is controlled by the `textconv`
# key on the `exif` / `imgdiff` diff drivers — set these once per clone
# (see `README.md` or run `tools/setup_image_diff.sh`):
#
#     git config diff.exif.textconv exiftool
#     # or, without external deps:
#     git config diff.imgdiff.textconv "file -b"
#
# Unconfigured clones fall back to Git's default "Binary files ...
# differ" behavior — no regression.
*.png       diff=exif
*.jpg       diff=exif
*.jpeg      diff=exif
*.webp      diff=exif
*.gif       diff=exif
